, high tourism and capital investment. Drawn from extreme island scenarios, the ten case studies in this volume review practices and policies for effective heritage management and offer rich descriptive and analytic material about land-use conflict. In addition, they point to interesting, new directions in which research, public policy and heritage management intersect.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 07. Nov 2022) 0aCultural propertyxEnvironmental aspects. 0aEconomic development. 0aIslandsxEnvironmental aspects. 0aOverpopulation. 0aReal estate development. 0aTourismxEnvironmental aspects. 7aNATURE / Environmental Conservation & Protection.2bisacsh1 aAttard, René, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBaldacchino, Godfrey, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBaldacchino, Godfrey, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aBungitak, John, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aCamilleri, Marguerite, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aCassinelli, Eleonora, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aConti, Joseph Magro, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aCover, Heather, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aDavid, Charles, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aFeu, Tim A. du, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aFurt, Jean-Marie, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGalea, Roberta, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGambin, Marie Therese, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHili, Monique, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/r